resources.string:
🟢 Mode "Word":
- searches for a standalone word in its exact form;
- "rocket" matches "a rocket is flying", but not "rockets" or "rocketry";
- "nd" matches "alert in nd", but not "fundament".

🟢 Mode "All words":
- all entered words must be present (order does not matter);
- each word is matched exactly — "rocket" will not match "rockets" or "rocketry";
- separate with space, comma, dash, or +;
- "rocket + kharkiv" matches "rocket flying to Kharkiv", but not "rockets over Kharkiv" and not "rocket flying to Kyiv".

🟢 Mode "Phrase":
- searches for an exact sequence of words;
- do not use quotation marks;
- "rocket to kharkiv" matches only when this exact phrase is present.

☝️ Letter case is ignored in all modes (uppercase/lowercase does not affect matching).

💡 Tip:
- use "All words" or "Phrase" for precise alerts;
- use "Word" for broader alerts;
- in "Word" mode, typing multiple words will automatically switch to "All words" (2–6 words) or "Phrase" (7+ words);
- to enter a phrase directly — wrap the text in quotes: "rocket to the city";
- after your first alert, open the Logs screen and copy the words you need directly from there.
